# Vembrane — Complete usage reference

**Source:** [vembrane/docs](https://github.com/vembrane/vembrane/tree/main/docs) and [vembrane README](https://github.com/vembrane/vembrane). High-level overview: **https://vembrane.github.io**.

vembrane transforms VCF/BCF using Python expressions over `INFO`, `FORMAT`, `CHROM`, `POS`, `ID`, `REF`, `ALT`, `QUAL`, `FILTER`, and annotation field `ANN`/`CSQ`. Backends: pysam or cyvcf2.

---

## Common options (shared across subcommands)

| Option | Short | Meaning |
|--------|-------|--------|
| `--output`, `-o` | | Output path (default: stdout) |
| `--output-fmt`, `-O` | | `vcf` \| `bcf` \| `uncompressed-bcf` (where applicable) |
| `--annotation-key`, `-k` | | INFO key for annotations (default `ANN`; use `CSQ` for VEP) |
| `--aux NAME=PATH`, `-a` | | Auxiliary file: one item per line, loaded as set; use as `AUX["NAME"]` in expressions |
| `--context CONTEXT` | | Python statement added to expression context (not sandboxed) |
| `--context-file PATH` | | Python script: globals/functions available in expressions (not sandboxed) |
| `--ontology PATH` | | OBO ontology; use `SO` in expressions; default built-in from sequenceontology.org if `SO` used |
| `--overwrite-number-info FIELD=NUMBER` | | Override INFO number (e.g. `cosmic_CNT=.`) |
| `--overwrite-number-format FIELD=NUMBER` | | Override FORMAT number (e.g. `DP=2`) |
| `--backend {cyvcf2,pysam}`, `-b` | | Reading backend (default: cyvcf2) |

---

## 1. `vembrane filter`

**Usage:** `vembrane filter [options] expression [input vcf/bcf]` — input can be omitted to read from stdin.

**Options (filter-specific):** `--keep-unmatched` (keep all annotations if at least one passes; SnpSift-like), `--preserve-order` (for BNDs).

**Expression:** Any Python expression that evaluates to `bool`. Use `bool()`, `any()`, `all()` for truthy/aggregation.

**Allowed in expressions:** `all`, `any`; `abs`, `len`, `max`, `min`, `round`, `sum`; `enumerate`, `filter`, `iter`, `map`, `next`, `range`, `reversed`, `sorted`, `zip`; `dict`, `list`, `set`, `tuple`; `bool`, `chr`, `float`, `int`, `ord`, `str`; `math.*`; `statistics.*`; `re.*`; custom: `without_na(iterable)`, `replace_na(iterable, replacement)`; genotype: `count_hom`, `count_het`, `count_any_ref`, `count_any_var`, `count_hom_ref`, `count_hom_var`, `is_hom(sample)`, `is_het(sample)`, `is_hom_ref(sample)`, `is_hom_var(sample)`, `has_ref(sample)`, `has_var(sample)`.

**Available fields in expressions:**

| Name | Type | Example |
|------|------|---------|
| `INFO` | `Dict[str, Any]` | `INFO["DP"] > 0` |
| `ANN` | Dict (annotation key from `-k`) | `ANN["SYMBOL"] == "CDH2"` |
| `CHROM` | `str` | `CHROM == "chr2"` |
| `POS` | `int` | `24 < POS < 42` |
| `END` | `int` | also `INFO["END"]` |
| `ID`, `REF`, `ALT` | `str` | |
| `QUAL` | `float` | `QUAL >= 30` |
| `FILTER` | `List[str]` | `"PASS" in FILTER` |
| `FORMAT` | `Dict[str, Dict[str, Any]]` | `FORMAT["DP"][SAMPLES[0]] > 0` |
| `SAMPLES` | `List[str]` | `"Tumor" in SAMPLES` |
| `INDEX` | `int` | |

**Missing values:** Annotation/INFO/FORMAT missing → `NA`. Compare with `NA` is always False; use `INFO["DP"] is NA`, `ID is not None`. Attribute access on `NA` returns `NA`. `re.search(..., NA)` treats NA as empty string.

**Multi-allelic:** vembrane does not split multi-allelics; preprocess with e.g. `bcftools norm -m-any`, GATK LeftAlignAndTrimVariants (split-multi-allelics), or vcfmulti2oneallele.

**Examples:**
```sh
vembrane filter 'ANN["SYMBOL"] == "CDH2" and ANN["Annotation_Impact"] == "HIGH"' variants.bcf
vembrane filter 'QUAL >= 30' variants.vcf
vembrane filter 'ANN["Protein_position"].start < 10' variants.bcf
vembrane filter 'bool(re.search("^rs[0-9]+", ID or ""))' variants.vcf
vembrane filter 'not {"pathogenic","likely_pathogenic"}.isdisjoint(ANN["CLIN_SIG"])' variants.vcf
vembrane filter 'FORMAT["DP"][SAMPLES[0]] > 0' variants.vcf
vembrane filter 'is_het("kid") and is_hom_ref("mom") and is_hom_ref("dad")' variants.vcf
vembrane filter --aux genes=genes.txt "ANN['SYMBOL'] in AUX['genes']" variants.vcf
vembrane filter --ontology so.obo 'ANN["Consequence"].any_is_a("intron_variant")' variants.vcf
```

**Ontology (SO):** `SO.get_id(term)`, `SO.get_term(id_)`; `terms.most_specific_terms()`; `term.ancestors()`, `term.descendants()`, `term.parents()`, `term.children()`; `term.is_a(parent)`, `terms.any_is_a(parent)`; `term.is_ancestor(other)`, `term.is_descendant(other)`; `term.path_length(target)`.

