## 3. `vembrane table`

**Usage:** `vembrane table [options] expression [vcf]` — expression is a comma-separated tuple defining columns. Use `ALL` to dump all INFO/FORMAT/ANN columns.

**Options:** `--separator CHAR` (default `\t`), `--header auto|none|comma_separated`, `--naming-convention dictionary|underscore|slash` (for `ALL`), `--wide` (one column per sample), `--long` (default; SAMPLE column + per-sample rows).

**Long format:** First column `SAMPLE`; variable `SAMPLE` available in expressions.  
**Wide format:** Use `for_each_sample(lambda sample: expr)` in the expression (and optionally in `--header`); one argument lambda, same number of fields.

```sh
vembrane table 'CHROM, POS, 10**(-QUAL/10), ANN["CLIN_SIG"]' input.vcf > table.tsv
vembrane table 'CHROM, POS, FORMAT["AD"][SAMPLE]/FORMAT["DP"][SAMPLE]*QUAL' input.vcf > long_table.tsv
vembrane table --wide 'CHROM, POS, for_each_sample(lambda s: FORMAT["DP"][s])' input.vcf > table.tsv
vembrane table 'ALL' input.vcf > table.tsv
```

